    • Constructor Detail

      • JsonParser

        public JsonParser(com.google.firebase.firestore.GeoPoint startGeo,
                  com.google.firebase.firestore.GeoPoint destGeo,
                  String API_KEY)
        This parses the json file from the url created for longitude and latitude. The information extracted is used for a riders ride request, Setters are not needed Purposes: - When a rider makes a new ride request the places/maps/directions API used to parse JSON files from the request made then use the information extracted from class to store ride requests from the Firebase DB. - It parses information (if there is any - some longitude and latitude may be null - UNHANDLED CASE) from a start and end location via google. This can be used to get the actual address of a place. Check the JSON file in the log tagged "urldirection" for a link to the JSON file.
        Parameters:
        startGeo -
        destGeo -
        API_KEY -
